The paper deals with the problem of combining information from diverse sources to make an inference about an objective ground truth, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes a noise model and auxiliary information set to improve voting outcomes, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and information theory (cs.IT).
